original: Holmstrand, Hjalmar Natanael, kyrkoherde emeritus, Borås, f. 25/11/ 72 i Blidsberg, Älvsb. 1, av kommin. Anders H. o. Johanna Charlotta Johansdotter. G. 03 m. Märta Karlén. Barn: Rut f. 05, g. 31 m. med. dr Per Linton, Växjö, Ivar 07, tandl., Sthlm, Karin 08, g. 31 m. textiling. Per Es-selius, Borås, Ingeborg 10, g. 35 m. folksk :lär. Olof Olausson, Alem, Bengt 12, stadsiarkit,.,, Lidiköp., Margit 14, g. 38 m. kommin. Ragnar Eriksson, Gbg, Lennart 18, past :adj., Bertdil 20, piastradj., Anna Märta 2!2i, g. 44 m. disp. Karl Gustaf Heintz, Hindås, Gunnar 23, fänrik. — Mogiex. i Skara 91, teol. fil. ex. 93, teor. teol. ex., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Skara stift 97. Tjg. i Husaby, Ryda, Rånge-dala, Hassle, Österplana o. Otterstad, kyrkoh. i Toarp 14, emeritus 46. LVO.
translated: Holmstrand, Hjalmar Natanael, retired vicar, Borås, born on November 25th 1872 in Blidsberg, Älvsborg County, son of assistant vicar Anders H. and Johanna Charlotta Johansdotter. Married in 1903 to Märta Karlén. Children: Rut, born in 1905, married in 1931 to Dr. Per Linton, Växjö; Ivar, born in 1907, dentist in Stockholm; Karin, born in 1908, married in 1931 to Per Es-selius, Borås, in the textile business; Ingeborg, born in 1910, married in 1935 to a primary school teacher named Olof Olausson in Alem; Bengt, born in 1912, city archivist in Lidköping; Margit, born in 1914, married in 1938 to vicar Ragnar Eriksson, Gothenburg; Lennart, born in 1918, assistant pastor; Bertdil, born in 1920, parish pastor; Anna Märta, born in 1922, married in 1944 to Karl Gustaf Heintz, Hindås, in the trade industry; Gunnar, born in 1923, second lieutenant. Graduated from Skara College in 1891, bachelor's degree in theology in 1893, theoretical theological degree, practical theological examination, and ordination for the Skara diocese in 1897. Served in Husaby, Ryda, Rångedala, Hassle, Österplana, and Otterstad before becoming vicar in Toarp in 1914. Retired in 1946. Holds the Order of Vasa.
